+**I7: Operations Agent state isolation.** The Operations Agent executes the
+mechanical merge procedure and produces a merge report. It does not advance
+protocol state, does not make go/no-go decisions, does not launch Wave or Scout
+agents, and does not modify agent prompts. Only the Orchestrator reads the merge
+report and advances state. Any action the Ops Agent takes that causes a state
+transition — including launching another agent or modifying an agent prompt
+section in the IMPL doc — is an I7 violation; stop and record the situation in
+`halt_reason` of the merge report instead.
