+**E15: Operations Agent launch criteria.** The Orchestrator may launch an
+Operations Agent instead of running the merge procedure inline when all three
+conditions hold: the wave has ≥2 agents, the build/test cycle is expected to
+exceed 30 seconds, and user interactivity during verification is desirable. When
+an Ops Agent is used, its SAW tag is `[SAW:ops:wave{N}] merge + verify wave N`.
+The Orchestrator reads the Ops Agent's merge report, reviews all deviations, and
+makes the go/no-go decision before launching the next wave. Using the Ops Agent
+does not change the go/no-go authority; it changes only who runs the build. The
+base merge procedure in `prompts/saw-merge.md` remains the default; the Ops Agent
+is an optimization, not a requirement.
